heck\n\nBefore doing any work, see if we’ve already computed `F(k)`.\n\n```python\n        if k in memo:\n            return memo[k]\n```\n\n**Why this check comes early?**\n- It prevents recomputing overlapping subproblems.\n- In Fibonacci, many calls repeatedly ask for the same `F(k)`.\n\n---\n\n## Step 6: Recursively compute and store\n\nIf not cached, compute:\n\n- `F(k) = F(k-1) + F(k-2)`\n\nThen store:\n\n```python\n        memo[k] = helper(k - 1) + helper(k - 2)\n        return memo[k]\n```\n\n**Why store after computing?**\n- We compute the value first (so we’re correct),\n- then cache it so any future request for `F(k)` is O(1).\n\n---\n\n## Step 7: Return the final result\n\n```python\n    return helper(n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Complete working implementation\n\n```python\ndef fib(n: int) -> int:\n    if not isinstance(n, int):\n        raise TypeError(\"n must be an integer\")\n    if n < 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"n must be non-negative\")\n\n    memo = {}\n\n    def helper(k: int) -> int:\n        if k == 0:\n            return 0\n        if k == 1:\n            return 1\n\n        if k in memo:\n            return memo[k]\n\n        memo[k] = helper(k - 1) + helper(k - 2)\n        return memo[k]\n\n    return helper(n)\n```\n\nExample usage:\n```python\nprint(fib(6))  # 8\nprint(fib(10)) # 55\n```\n\n---\n\n## Note on recursion depth (practical design consideration)\nThis approach uses recursion, so for large `n` (roughly > 900–1000), Python may hit the recursion limit. For very large `n`, an iterative DP version avoids that.\n\n---\n\n## (Optional) Alternative: Python’s built-in memoization\nPython can do memoization automatically via `functools.lru_cache`:\n\n```python\nfrom functools import lru_cache\n\n@lru_cache(maxsize=None)\ndef fib(n: int) -> int:\n    if n < 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"n must be non-negative\")\n    if n < 2:\n        return n\n    return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2)\n```\n\nThis is functionally the same idea, but you avoid manually managing the `memo` dict.\n\n"},"sequence_number":975}

